  "texts": [
    "Another interesting defnition for our analysis is the one proposed by Goertzel and Pennacin in their 2007 book Artifcial General Intelligence:",
    "Artifcial General Intelligence (AGI) refers to AI research in which \"intelligence\" is understood as a general-purpose capability, not restricted to any narrow collection of problems or domains and including the ability to broadly generalize to fundamentally new areas.",
    "(Goertzel & Pennachin, 2007) The various defnitions of AGI often recall a cross-cutting capability of the language model, defned as \"general-purpose.\"",
    "Moreover, in their latest blog post \"How should AI systems behave, and who should decide?, 9 \" they open with the sentence \"OpenAI's mission is to ensure that artifcial general intelligence (AGI 10) benefts all of humanity.\"",
    "11 If we are taking GPT-3 as a case study, it is because OpenAI defnes its API as follows: \"unlike most AI systems which are designed for one usecase, the API today provides a general-purpose \"text in, text out\" interface, allowing users to try it on virtually any English language task\" (Broackman et al., 2020)."
